      • getInitializedValue

        public Object getInitializedValue()
        Description copied from interface: EntityPropertyBinder
        Get the current value or initialize a new value if it has not been set. Use this method if you want to create intermediate bean paths because you want to update underlying properties of the entity.

        Using getInitializedValue() will also delegate any existing value to EntityPropertyController.createDto(EntityPropertyBindingContext, Object) for creating a DTO object that can be safely updated without directly applying the changes to the underlying entity it possibly represents.

        Specified by:
        getInitializedValue in interface EntityPropertyBinder
        Returns:
        the value and initialize a new value if necessary
        See Also:
        EntityPropertyBinder.createNewValue(), EntityPropertyController.createDto(EntityPropertyBindingContext, Object)

      • getEntryList

        public List<MapEntityPropertyBinder.Entry> getEntryList()
        Get an ordered - unmodifiable - list of all the entries in the map. These will be sorted according to the value of MapEntityPropertyBinder.Entry.getSortIndex().

        Includes all entries, including ones where MapEntityPropertyBinder.Entry.isDeleted() is true.

        Returns:
        unmodifiable list of all entries in order

      • enableBinding

        public void enableBinding(boolean enabled)
        While binding is enabled, the entries collection will not remove any (possibly) deleted entries. When explicitly disabling binding, the entries will be cleared of any deleted entries and will be fully cleared if the property itself is deleted.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true if in binding mode, false if not expecting any more changes

      • resolvePropertyBinder

        public EntityPropertyBinder resolvePropertyBinder(EntityPropertyDescriptor descriptor)
        Description copied from interface: EntityPropertyBinder
        Attempt to resolve a child property binder for the given property descriptor. The descriptor is expected to represent either the same property the current binder is for, or a child property.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - for the property you want to resolve
        Returns:
        property binder

      • isUpdateEntriesOnBinding

        public boolean isUpdateEntriesOnBinding()
        If set to true, the existing entries will always be returned when performing data binding, and every entry separately can be removed/modified. If false, then it is expected that all entries are passed when data binding (replacing them). The latter is the default mode.

      • setUpdateEntriesOnBinding

        public void setUpdateEntriesOnBinding(boolean updateEntriesOnBinding)
        If set to true, the existing entries will always be returned when performing data binding, and every entry separately can be removed/modified. If false, then it is expected that all entries are passed when data binding (replacing them). The latter is the default mode.
